title: Document parse_single_sequence_example
body_html: The docs are completely silent on parse_single_sequence_example, even though the (officially referenced) tf.train.Example protocol buffers documentation mentions SequenceExample, and the documentation for parse_single_sequence_example in the source code (parsing_ops.py) appears rather complete. I think just exposing the source code documentation would be very helpful to people. In general though SequenceExample could use better documentation as it's a very useful feature.

body: The docs are completely silent on `parse_single_sequence_example`, even though the (officially referenced) `tf.train.Example` protocol buffers documentation mentions `SequenceExample`, and the documentation for `parse_single_sequence_example` in the source code (parsing_ops.py) appears rather complete. I think just exposing the source code documentation would be very helpful to people. In general though `SequenceExample` could use better documentation as it's a very useful feature.
